The Minister of Communications, Ms Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams presents the 4IRSA partnership and unveils plans towards the Digital Economy Summit through a media launch at the Tshimologong Precinct in Braamfontein. 4IRSA is a partnership between Telkom and the Universities of Witwatersrand, Fort Hare and Johannesburg. The partnership seeks to stimulate and facilitate an inclusive national dialogue to shape a coherent national response to the 4th Industrial Revolution (4IR) in South Africa.  